<section class="container section" id="caesar-demo">
    <div class="row justify-content-center">
        <div class="col-lg-10">
            <h2 class="section-title text-center mb-5 fade-in">Interactive Caesar Cipher</h2>
            
            <div class="card fade-in">
                <div class="card-header">
                    <h3 class="mb-0"><i class="fas fa-cog"></i> Cipher Playground</h3>
                </div>
                <div class="card-body">
                    <div class="form-group">
                        <label for="caesar-input">Plain Text:</label>
                        <input type="text" id="caesar-input" class="form-control" placeholder="Enter text to encrypt" value="HELLO WORLD">
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="form-group">
                        <label for="caesar-shift">Shift Value (1-25):</label>
                        <input type="range" id="caesar-shift" class="form-control-range" min="1" max="25" value="3">
                        <div class="text-center mt-2">
                            <span id="shift-value">3</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="output-container code-block" data-language="encrypted">
                        <code id="caesar-output">KHOOR ZRUOG</code>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="cipher-explanation mt-4">
                        <h4><i class="fas fa-info-circle"></i> How It Works</h4>
                        <p>The Caesar cipher is one of the simplest encryption techniques. It works by shifting each letter in the plaintext by a fixed number of positions down the alphabet.</p>
                        <pre class="code-block mt-3" data-language="example">
A → D (shift 3)
B → E (shift 3)
C → F (shift 3)
...and so on</pre>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

